SIMPLE: chromatrope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chromatrope
<hw>Chro"ma*trope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ color +
<?/ turn, rotation, <?/ to turn.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>An instrument for exhibiting certain chromatic effects of light
(depending upon the persistence of vision and mixture of colors) by
means of rapidly rotating disks variously colored.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A device in a magic lantern or stereopticon to
produce kaleidoscopic effects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chromatype</ent>⟦br⟧
